                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2516a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-10T19:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 10, 1936—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>304. A press report this afternoon from London states that the French Government
                    is preparing to invite the American Government to adhere to the proposed
                    European Pact of Non-intervention in the Spanish civil war.</p>
                <p>Please telegraph at once any information which you can obtain respecting the
                    correctness of this report. A similar telegram is being sent to London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
